From f4d9336390a2e15256ad7c733dc30b3b5e430c6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: utzcoz <utzcoz@outlook.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:18:15 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] vr: add WebXR-over-OpenXR support on Linux

Enables Chromium's WebXR stack to create immersive-vr sessions on
Linux through the OpenXR API, tested with Monado, the reference
OpenXR runtime for Linux.

Platform backend:
- OpenXrPlatformHelperLinux: runtime discovery, instance lifecycle,
  hardware polling with cached XrInstance across session boundaries.
- OpenXrGraphicsBindingVulkan: creates VkInstance/VkDevice via
  XR_KHR_vulkan_enable2; allocates intermediate VkImages with
  LINEAR tiling exported as DMA-BUF (VK_KHR_external_memory_fd +
  VK_EXT_external_memory_dma_buf) for cross-API GPU sharing with
  GL; vkCmdCopyImage blit to the swapchain image each frame;
  vkImportSemaphoreFdKHR to consume the GL-signaled sync FD.
- Format negotiation caches the selected VkFormat in
  GetSwapchainFormat() so CreateSharedImages() creates intermediate
  images and SharedImages (kRGBA_8888 / kBGRA_8888) that match.
- Per-frame VkImageLayout is tracked on IntermediateImage so the
  pipeline barrier uses the correct oldLayout across frames, and
  a persistent VkFence scopes the CPU stall to the specific submit
  rather than all pending queue work.

VR browser overlay UI:
- Reuses chrome/browser/vr/graphics_delegate_win.{cc,h} on Linux
  (the "Win" name is historical; the implementation is pure
  GL-command-buffer + SharedImage and is cross-platform). Linux
  compiles it via BUILD.gn is_win||is_linux branch and gets
  gles2_c_lib for SetGLContext.
- chrome_xr_integration_client.cc returns VRUiHostImpl on every
  platform instead of nullptr on Linux.
- OpenXrGraphicsBindingVulkan::SetOverlayTexture imports the
  browser-side overlay DMA-BUF as a VkImage (DMA_BUF handle type
  via VK_EXT_external_memory_dma_buf). The VkImage is cached and
  re-imported only on size change.
- RenderLayer composites the overlay into the WebXR swapchain
  image with vkCmdBlitImage to a fixed screen-space rect per eye
  (40%-wide, 25%-tall, centered-lower). This is a first cut: no
  alpha blending, no head-locked world-space pose. Follow-up:
  replace with a shader-based quad draw for proper pose.

Build & integration:
- Flips enable_openxr for Linux in buildflags.gni.
- Adds Linux config to third_party/openxr/BUILD.gn (XR_OS_LINUX,
  XR_USE_GRAPHICS_API_VULKAN).
- Fixes openxr_platform.h to include vulkan_core.h on Linux.
- Fixes openxr_render_loop.h XRThread + thread.h for Linux.
- Fixes json_mock copy() empty-sources on Linux.
- Wires xr_runtime_provider.cc with parallel IS_LINUX blocks.
- Enables kOpenXR feature by default on Linux.
- Uses recommended (not max) swapchain image size on Linux.
- Keeps XRRuntimeManagerImpl alive across navigations via
  base::NoDestructor<scoped_refptr<>>, the Chromium-idiomatic form
  of an intentional singleton leak (crbug.com/397907158).
